<subSubSection id="B299C2A587BA9B64EE4D25B9A0F2BED8" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="2FA53C5AE0634E53D5A580630C377ED3" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="43B6873F6E3BBBB049E8E8510D3B84A1" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
This is a range-restricted subspecies, endemic to the eastern part of the Balkan Peninsula. In Greece, it is only known from the mountains of the NE floristic region: Athos, Belles, Pangeo, Menikio, Orvilos, Falakro and Rodopi (
<bibRefCitation id="F4BD55652C90E46470D98351FEAA2422" author="Strid, A." journalOrPublisher="Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7669399" refString="Strid, A., 1997. Flora Hellenica 1. Koeltz Scientific Books, Koenigstein" title="Flora Hellenica 1" year="1997">Strid 1997b</bibRefCitation>
). The new locality on Mt. Achladovouno extends the Greek distribution of the subspecies to the east.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
